Sentencas: AC complex impedance spectroscopy studies were conducted between 600 and 800 C on symmetrical cells that employed strontium-and-magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte, La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM).
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: The objective of the study was to identify the materials system for fabrication and evaluation of intermediate-temperature (600-800 degrees C) solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: The slurry-coated electrode materials had fine porosity to enhance catalytic activity.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: Cathode materials investigated include La1-xSrxMnO3 (LSM), LSCF (La1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3), a two-phase particulate composite consisting of LSM-doped-lanthanum gallate (LSGM), and LSCF-LSGM.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: The anode materials were Ni-Ce0.85Gd0.15O2 (Ni-GDC) and Ni-Ce0.6La0.4O2 (Ni-LDC) composites.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: Experiments conducted with the anode materials investigated the effect of having a barrier layer of GDC or LDC in between the LSGM electrolyte and the Ni-composite anode to prevent adverse reaction of the Ni with lanthanum in LSGM.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: For proper interpretation of the beneficial effects of the barrier layer, similar measurements were performed without the barrier layer.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: The ohmic and the polarization resistances of the system were obtained over time as a function of temperature (600-800 degrees C), firing temperature, thickness, and the composition of the electrodes.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte

Sentencas: The study revealed important details pertaining to the ohmic and polarization resistances of the electrode as they relate to stability and the charge-transfer reactions that occur in such electrode structures.
Titulo: Materials system for intermediate-temperature (600-800°C) SOFCs based on doped lanthanum-gallate electrolyte
